eds the ADR decision. No comments. [...] **chirp#30** — OPEN. Labels: enhancement. Proposes an "X-Ray Feed" developer overlay showing live relay-subscription reconciliation with causal chains, staged in three phases: v0 "Shadow X-Ray" (buildable now, visualizes NMP's discarded shadow ResourcePlan next to legacy behavior — now stale since #2808 already promoted shadow to authority), v1 "Authority X-Ray" (real applied commands with causal chains, gated on #2808 — now closed/done), v2 "Time travel" (record + scrub a session trace, gated on trellis#114 — now closed/done — and NMP#2809). Explicitly out of scope: metrics/dashboards/log views, receipts only. No comments. [...] **5. [Should-fix — Phase A] "Compiled out of release builds" needs a mechanical definition and CI enforcement.** `cfg(debug_assertions)` is the wrong tool (release-with-debug builds exist; per-platform build configs differ). Suggested wording: nmp-devtools is a separate crate behind an off-by-default cargo feature; CI asserts each platform's release artifact dependency graph (`cargo tree`) and/or symbol table contains no nmp-devtools; the ratchet rule is dependency-graph-based — an allowlist file of crates permitted to depend on `trellis-*` (existing private adapters + nmp-devtools), where adding a line is the ratchet violation.
