c7805-80f5b | 2026-07-03T07:47:50Z | session:c7805f5d-42c5-44b6-8eaa-ecd2453ed822 | Assistant: **Epic created: [nostr-multi-platform#2858](https://github.com/pablof7z/nostr-multi-platform/issues/2858)** — no epic existed before (the surveyor confirmed nothing ties this workstream together; the closest ancestors, NMP #2626/#2627, are closed). I cross-linked it from chirp#30 and NMP#2809, and yes: **time travel is in the plan as committed scope (Phase E), not a stretch goal** — per your message, it's written up as the recorded/replayable debugging capsule with scrubbing, not log viewing. [...] User: help me carve out a plan, this is coming from Trellis recommendations to be able to land Chirp issue 30. don't implement anything -- just help me with a plan -- should we aim for the time-travel thing? [...] One reuse note the surveyor surfaced: Trellis's **Flight Recorder workstation** (trellis#160, merged today) is already a full trace-replay UI — provenance, transaction timeline, receipt inspector, replay tabs. Phase E should feed NMP capsules into it for desktop-side inspection rather than building a second scrubber; the epic says so. [...] **16. [Consider — Phase E] Ring buffer needs a byte bound, not just a count.** One teardown-cascade transaction can be enormous (the trace carries every command, frame, and audit entry). Bound by bytes and count. [...] **2. [Blocker — Phase E] "Replay from capsule alone" conflates scrubbing with re-execution.** `TransactionTrace` records what happened, payload-free; you cannot re-execute from traces. Re-execution requires the `DataTransactionScript` (operations *with payloads* — follow lists, filters), plus the same NMP version constructing the identical graph topology, because NodeIds are positional. Recording the script blows up the privacy surface far beyond the payload-free trace. Suggested change: define capsule v1 explicitly as **trace + receipts, scrub/reconstruction only**; document `replay_session(trace)` as reconstruction,