.toml:16:  nostr = { version = "0.44", default-features = false, features = ["nip44", "nip59"] } \n ``` \n  \n (c) Feature composition: yes, `{ workspace = true, features = ["std","nip44","nip60"] }` WOULD compose correctly (Cargo features are additive, and nip60 wants defaults-on, matching the bare workspace posture). So it's technically migratable — but the maintainers chose not to, workspace-wide, and documented why. The "will drift on the next workspace nostr bump" concern applies equally to ~10 crates and is an accepted, tracked deferral, not a defect introduced by this PR. \n  \n The candidate's factual premise (serde/serde_json migrated to `workspace = true` while nostr stays pinned in nip60) is correct — confirmed at nmp-nip60/Cargo.toml lines 16-18 — but the "half-migration bug" framing is wrong: it's consistent with siblings and with an explicit in-repo policy boundary. [...] **Verified non-issues worth knowing:** the field rename cannot break persisted wallets (relays live in tags, config JSON is hand-built key-pairs); the `nostr = "0.44"` literal pin is an explicit documented workspace policy boundary, not a missed migration; the kind:38172 exclusive claim without design-doc mention matches workspace norm (nmp-nip57/nmp-blossom do the same); and the release dry-run only runs `cargo package --list` over the new `[[public_crates]]` entry, with all path deps also public.
