c7805-ad91f | 2026-07-03T09:41:01Z | session:c7805f5d-42c5-44b6-8eaa-ecd2453ed822 | - **[NMP #2864](https://github.com/pablof7z/nostr-multi-platform/issues/2864)** — Epic: NIP-60/61 wallet milestone. Six phases straight from the design doc: reactivate `nmp-nip60` → `nmp-wallet` composition crate (WalletBackend seam + operation journal) → NWC consolidation behind the seam → NIP-60 Cashu wallet → NIP-61 nutzap send/receive → Chirp UX. Plus the doc's invariants (fail-closed, no secrets in projections, thin shells) and its full test-gate list. [...] 2. **Binds one typed projection** (`"wallet"`) — backend readiness, capability flags, balances by mint/unit, pending operations by correlation id, bounded history. The projection **never** contains keys, Cashu proofs, or secrets. UI enables buttons off capability flags: if the backend can't melt to Lightning, there is no melt button — an absent capability, never a runtime error. [...] **Your app does exactly two things:** \n  \n 1. **Dispatches typed actions** — `nmp.wallet.cashu.create`, `cashu.deposit_quote`, `nutzap.send`, `nutzap.redeem`, `pay_invoice`, … Fire-and-forget with a correlation id; no return values across FFI. \n 2. **Binds one typed projection** (`"wallet"`) — backend readiness, capability flags, balances by mint/unit, pending operations by correlation id, bounded history. The projection **never** contains keys, Cashu proofs, or secrets. UI enables buttons off capability flags: if the backend can't melt to Lightning, there is no melt button — an absent capability, never a runtime error. \n  \n **What the kernel does underneath, using "send a nutzap" as the example:** your action arrives → `nmp-wallet` resolves the recipient's kind:10019 (their accepted mints, relays, and P2PK pubkey) through normal kernel reads — and **fails closed as state** if they don't have one → selects your proofs, swaps them at the mint into P2PK-locked proofs (every value-moving step recorded first in a durable **operation journal**,