06529-0f95c | 2026-07-03T10:05:54Z | session:065295ad-311d-4965-a3c1-6f749135f2b8 | Two tiers. The schema file is explicit that only local tables are canonical; `relay_*` are rebuildable projections (`src/state/schema.rs:1-7`, `:129`). \n  \n ### A. SQLite — non-rebuildable local truth (`src/state/schema.rs`) \n - **`sessions`** `:131` — the canonical local process record. PK `session_id`; carries `agent_pubkey, channel_h, child_pid, alive, last_seen, working, turn_started_at, last_distill_at, title, activity, resume_id`. This is *the* per-session state; the runtime task is "a thin driver over the local `sessions` row" (`src/runtime.rs:11`). \n - **`session_channels`** `:153` — joined-channel set per session (PK `(session_id, channel_h)`). The input set that drives subscription coverage and status `h`-tags. \n - **`session_aliases`** `:162` — harness/pane/pid → canonical `session_id` mapping. \n - **`identities`** `:175` — ordinal (agent, machine) pubkey bindings; `base_pubkey, ordinal, session_id, channel_h, alive`. \n - **`inbox`** `:191` — delivery ledger, PK `(event_id, target_session)`, `state='pending'`. The per-session mention queue. \n - **`outbox`** `:205` — durable signed-event publish queue (`event_json, state, retries, last_error`). \n - **`project_roots`** `:216` — `channel_h → abs_path` on this machine. \n  \n ### B. SQLite — `relay_*` materialized caches (rebuildable projections) \n `relay_channels:18`, `relay_channel_members:27`, `relay_channel_member_sets:37`, `relay_profiles:44`, `relay_status:53`, `relay_events:71`, `relay_event_quarantine:88`, `messages:101`, `message_recipients:119`. These are filled solely by the inbound materializer (§3) and every comment marks a write failure as "relay truth diverged from cache" (e.g. `materializer.rs:40`).
