06529-53f53 | 2026-07-04T17:59:57Z | session:065295ad-311d-4965-a3c1-6f749135f2b8 | ### 3.7 Time-travel: record & replay — `tenex-edge probe record` / `probe replay <capsule>` \n  \n *Reproduce any past window of decisions; assert trace equality; step it in the Flight Recorder.* The insight from reading the code: the natural record point is **the drive seam, not an input journal**. `journal.rs`'s `InputFact` vocabulary exists but nothing consumes it — the real reconcilers take typed host-shaped calls (`sync(&CoverageSnapshot)`, `on_distill(id,title,activity,now)`, `render_context(...)`). So: \n  \n - Record: an opt-in ring-buffered JSONL **drive log** per surface — each entry is `{surface, method, args, at}` with serde derives added to `CoverageSnapshot`, the status method args, and `ViewInputs`. This is `HookCallLog`'s proven pattern (`command_forensics.rs` env-gated JSONL) aimed at the reconciler boundary. Bounded by bytes *and* count (X-Ray's lesson: one teardown cascade can be enormous). \n - Replay: `probe replay capsule.jsonl` rebuilds a fresh reconciler and re-drives it via `trellis-testing`'s `TrellisHarness::replay_data` + `DataTransactionScript` (`harness.rs:117-126`) — which gives us, for free, `assert_replay_matches` (trace equality + final `debug_dump` equality + ledger equality), the `ResourceLedger` (dup-close/orphan/forbidden detection), and the `OutputLedger` (revision monotonicity). Determinism claim, falsified or confirmed on demand. \n - Export: `--export-trace out.json` writes a `SerializedScenario` (v-pinned) that **loads directly into the existing Flight Recorder workstation** — timeline, phase ladder, receipt inspector, all for free. \n  [...] ### 4.4 Replay capsules (adopt — richer than flattened receipts) \n  \n The critique is right that counterfactual/acid are only cheap once we persist **input capsules**, not just receipts. The natural record point (from reading the code) is the **drive seam**, and the vocabulary is `InputFact` — already