06529-6827f | 2026-07-04T18:00:45Z | session:065295ad-311d-4965-a3c1-6f749135f2b8 | **Hook context is Trellis-derived, but not live-graph authoritative in the same sense.** The reconciler correctly models the fabric snapshot as declared inputs → derived `FabricView` → materialized output frame, with cursor and `now` explicit.  But the actual turn-start and turn-check paths instantiate `HookContextReconciler::new()` inside each assembly function.   That means there is no long-lived hook-context graph in the daemon to inspect the way there is for status/subscriptions. \n  \n **The input-journal idea exists, but it is not yet the live driver.** `InputFact` models the canonical facts Trellis should receive, and its comments say each variant names the writer it will eventually replace.  But `rpc_turn_start` still directly calls `set_working` and `set_session_transcript` before context assembly.  `rpc_session_start` still directly resolves, writes aliases/project roots, upserts the session row, checks relay readiness, admits signers, subscribes, spawns the engine, and emits tail events. [...] Bonus confirmation of the critique's sharpest point: the hook_context reconciler is instantiated fresh per render (`turn_context/start.rs:221`, `check.rs:94`) and discarded. There is no live hook graph to inspect. The critique is right; `probe why hook` against "the live graph" is currently impossible. \n  [...] ### 4.3 Live graphs for ALL surfaces + `probe why` + `probe state` \n  \n - **Fix hook_context (the critique's #1 correctness point).** Promote it from `advisory` to `authoritative` by holding a **long-lived per-session `HookContextReconciler` in `DaemonState`** keyed by session id, instead of `HookContextReconciler::new()` per render. The reconciler is already designed for reuse (its node-set is "re-pointed each render," `mod.rs:20-21,106-109`); nothing but the *call site* needs to change. Then `probe why hook:<session>` queries the *actual* graph the agent's last injection came from, and the acid test verifies the real artifact, not a reconstruction. \n - `probe state [surface]` — live values under the reconciler lock: subscription owner sets + refcounts (`resource_owners`/`owner_count`, `subscriptions/mod.rs:243`), scope inventories (`scope_resource_inventory`, `audit.rs:40`), status inputs + derived `StatusCommand`, hook inputs + `FabricView`. `--dump` emits `graph.debug_dump()` verbatim (`debug.rs`). [...] ### Graph / output shape \n Six inputs — `cursor: i64`, `now: i64`, and the four canonical store sources modelled as distinct nodes (`channel-meta`, `members`, `presence`, `messages`) → one derived `fabric-view` node → one `hook-context-snapshot` materialized output. Captures are **now/cursor-independent supersets** (all statuses regardless of NIP-40 expiration; all chat since 0), so the `expiration >= now` liveness window, the `created_at > since` chat window, the full-vs-delta **shape** decision, and every `relative_time` string are pure functions of the `cursor`/`now` inputs inside `assemble_view` — not ambient reads. Because the derive reads only declared inputs (an undeclared read is a Trellis error), the old awareness/render scope mismatch is impossible by construction. \n  \n ### Cutover \n `assemble_turn_start` / `assemble_turn_check` keep their membership-warning / inbox-drain / cursor-advance logic but now `capture_inputs()` → `render_context()`; the injected text comes from the output frame's `FabricView` fed to the existing `render.rs` stringifier (byte-identical). The receipt — sourced from `why_output_frame`/`why_changed`, **not a re-derivation** — replaces `turn_start_audit`/`turn_check_audit` and is emitted as the RPC `audit` (`kind` preserved for the debug loader). Text-only `*_context` shims (`#[cfg(test)]`) keep the ~15 hook-parity test call-sites unchanged. \n  \n ### Test evidence (verbatim) \n ``` \n test reconcile::hook_context::tests::cursor_drives_shape_and_is_attributed ... ok \n test reconcile::hook_context::tests::determinism_and_replay ... ok \n test reconcile::hook_context::tests::presence_change_attributed_to_presence_input ... ok \n test reconcile::hook_context::tests::unchanged_recommit_reuses_cached_view ... ok \n test reconcile::hook_context::tests::equivalence_with_legacy_build_view ... ok \n test result: ok. 400 passed; 0 failed; 0 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out; finished in 0.30s \n ``` \n - **Determinism/replay** — two independent graphs, same inputs+cursor+now → byte-identical snapshot AND identical `HookContextReceipt` (`Baseline` frame); `assert_oracle()` after each tx. \n - **Shape attribution** — `cursor==0` renders `<members>` (no `<recent-presence>`); `cursor>0` drops members, renders `<recent-presence>`; the flip's `receipt.input_causes` contains `"cursor"` and `why_view_causes()` contains the cursor input id. \n - **"Why is @X working"** — flipping a status busy/activity in the `presence` input moves the member line to `status="refactoring"`, the frame is `Delta`, `receipt.input_causes` contains `"presence"`, and `why_view_causes()` contains the presence input id — matching the rendered member. \n - **Regression equivalence** — for full (`cursor=0`) and delta (`cursor>0`), reconciler text `==` legacy `render_fabric_context` (old `build_view`) byte-for-byte. [...] - **Hook/fabric context** → derived `FabricView` → materialized output frame. **Deleted** the drifting `turn_start_audit`; the receipt now *is* the render's dependency trace and can't drift. Proven **byte-for-byte identical** to the old renderer. \n - **`tenex-edge explain`** → `llm_calls` + `receipts` stores joined by `window_hash`, queried over the daemon socket.
06529-b850b | 2026-07-04T18:00:47Z | session:065295ad-311d-4965-a3c1-6f749135f2b8 | Two falsifiable targets, adapted to tenex-edge (these are the case-study experiments, §7): \n  \n 1. **Diagnosis metric.** An off-the-shelf model, given *only* the serialized commit/trace stream around a **seeded** lifecycle bug (a subscription that fails to close; a status that republishes when it shouldn't), identifies root cause with ≥90% accuracy — versus its baseline from tenex-edge's raw `tracing` logs of the same incident. The delta is the publishable Story-3 result. \n 2. **Safety invariant.** On any surface at `authoritative` or above, **no host effect executes without a Trellis plan/frame having been produced first** — enforced structurally by the bypass ratchet (§4.5), not by convention. This is the operational form of "never gamble." \n  [...]  \n **Experiment A — the diagnosis metric (Story 3).** Seed a lifecycle bug (revert the refcount so a shared channel closes on first-owner departure, or disable status dedup). Run the incident twice: give a model (a) the serialized commit/trace stream + labels, (b) the raw `tracing` logs. Measure root-cause accuracy. Target ≥90% from receipts vs the log baseline; the delta is the publishable result and the literal demonstration of "diagnosis becomes lookup, not abduction." \n  \n **Experiment B — the safety invariant (Story 1).** Show, via the bypass ratchet + `probe simulate`, that on authoritative surfaces every effect was preceded by a previewed plan — "no effect without a machine-reviewable plan first," enforced structurally. \n  \n **Beachhead evidence tenex-edge already owns (Story 2 — lead with this).** The refcounted, close-on-last-owner subscription reconciler *already fixed a real unbounded leak* the old aggregate `SubscriptionRegistry` could not tear down (`subscriptions/mod.rs:1-25`, adoption doc §surfaces). `probe stats` quantifies it live: opens/closes/coalesced/`live_now`, "N closes emitted, 0 leaks." This is the "you have leaked subscriptions right now" story, told by a shipping consumer with numbers — the honest version NMP's shadow-mode adoption can't yet tell because it isn't authoritative.
